{"id": "1420619885465042954", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 0, "author_id": "108392615644278784", "author_name": "alistiel", "author_bot": false, "content": "Team's fine, then. As you level up you'll naturally end up replacing Goliath with Tulu.", "timestamp": "2025-09-25T03:56:14.536000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1420620486601216121", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 19, "author_id": "108392615644278784", "author_name": "alistiel", "author_bot": false, "content": "The teams are malleable enough that this is fine. \n\nUnits that rely on Strike cards to inflict damage lose a lot of steam later on because they just don't scale to the degree that they need to, so Uvhash ends up doing better later on. Helot's ultimate works on Lotan's strike cards, and Lotan's gimmick of using Strike is better than Helot's gimmick of using Prohibitively Expensive Strike, so Helot works out as a good support unit despite her assault designation. They're a B team combination for me, though, despite how much I leveled them.", "timestamp": "2025-09-25T03:58:37.858000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-09-25T03:59:00.527000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1420502601094398093", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1420620973161320499", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "type": 0, "author_id": "108392615644278784", "author_name": "alistiel", "author_bot": false, "content": "Slamming a powerful Exalt repeatedly is much better supported by other units and tends to be something that Uvhash does competitively even with other limited Awakers, so he goes the distance you need him to.", "timestamp": "2025-09-25T04:00:33.863000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
